            <fr:title text="Banach Space">Banach Space</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
            <fr:date>
              <fr:year>2025</fr:year>
              <fr:month>5</fr:month>
              <fr:day>26</fr:day>
            </fr:date>
            <fr:authors>
              <fr:author>Long Nguyen</fr:author>
            </fr:authors>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <fr:p>A Banach space is a complete <fr:link type="local" href="FA-002K.xml" addr="FA-002K" title="Normed Space">normed space</fr:link>.</fr:p>
            <fr:p>A normed space <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> is called a Banach space if every <fr:link type="local" href="FA-002L.xml" addr="FA-002L" title="Cauchy sequence">Cauchy sequence</fr:link> in <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> converges to an element in <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
          <fr:backmatter />
        </fr:tree>
        <fr:tree toc="true" numbered="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" expanded="false" root="false" xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml">
          <fr:frontmatter>
            <fr:anchor>1567</fr:anchor>
            <fr:addr type="user">FA-003E</fr:addr>
            <fr:route>FA-003E.xml</fr:route>
            <fr:title text="Essential Supremum">Essential Supremum</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
            <fr:date>
              <fr:year>2025</fr:year>
              <fr:month>5</fr:month>
              <fr:day>26</fr:day>
            </fr:date>
            <fr:authors>
              <fr:author>Long Nguyen</fr:author>
            </fr:authors>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <fr:p>The essential supremum of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[|f|]]></fr:tex> is the <fr:em>minimum</fr:em> <fr:link type="local" href="FA-003P.xml" addr="FA-003P" title="Essential Upper Bound">essential upper bound</fr:link> for <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[|f|]]></fr:tex>, 
namely the <fr:em>minimum</fr:em> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\alpha ]]></fr:tex> such that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[|f| \leq  \alpha ]]></fr:tex> <fr:link type="local" href="FA-003Q.xml" addr="FA-003Q" title="Almost Everywhere">almost everywhere</fr:link>.</fr:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
          <fr:backmatter />
        </fr:tree>
        <fr:tree toc="true" numbered="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" expanded="false" root="false" xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml">
          <fr:frontmatter>
            <fr:anchor>1569</fr:anchor>
            <fr:addr type="user">FA-003D</fr:addr>
            <fr:route>FA-003D.xml</fr:route>
            <fr:title text="Measurable Function">Measurable Function</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
            <fr:date>
              <fr:year>2025</fr:year>
              <fr:month>5</fr:month>
              <fr:day>26</fr:day>
            </fr:date>
            <fr:authors>
              <fr:author>Long Nguyen</fr:author>
            </fr:authors>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <fr:p>These are all equivalent definitions of <fr:strong>measurable functions</fr:strong>:</fr:p>
            <fr:ul><fr:li>For all <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\ \alpha  \in  \mathbb {R}]]></fr:tex>, the set <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\ \left \{ x \in  \Omega : f(x) > \alpha  \right \}]]></fr:tex> is Lebesgue measurable</fr:li>
  <fr:li>For all <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\ \alpha  \in  \mathbb {R}]]></fr:tex>, the set <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\ \left \{ x \in  \Omega : f(x) < \alpha  \right \}]]></fr:tex> is Lebesgue measurable</fr:li>
  <fr:li>For all <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\ \alpha  \in  \mathbb {R}]]></fr:tex>, the set <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\ \left \{ x \in  \Omega : f(x) \geq  \alpha  \right \}]]></fr:tex> is Lebesgue measurable</fr:li>
  <fr:li>For all <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\ \alpha  \in  \mathbb {R}]]></fr:tex>, the set <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\ \left \{ x \in  \Omega : f(x) \leq  \alpha  \right \}]]></fr:tex> is Lebesgue measurable</fr:li>
  <fr:li>For all <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[U \subset  \mathbb {R}]]></fr:tex>, the set <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\ \left \{ x \in  \Omega : f(x) \in  U \right \}]]></fr:tex> is Lebesgue measurable</fr:li></fr:ul>
          </fr:mainmatter>
          <fr:backmatter />
        </fr:tree>
